The other families involved as well.. 2 other children left behind without either of their parents or sister , children and a husband lost there wife&mom . snippet.textDisplay:
Even before she started talking I knew Tamara would be so emotional and I knew I would cry. Tamara is a parent and knows how wrong it is to lose a child. And the sentiment she expressed, we all feel it, Vanessa lost her husband and her daughter. To lose the love of your life, Kobe and your legacy Gianna. Your child is your life, your legacy.
Everyone on The Real is sad not just for themselves but for friends of Kobe that are grieving. Which I think is what the world is feeling. We are all seeking out comfort from others whether it be the videos or the comments. When Loni cried for Shaq, I sobbed.
I don't officially pray to God, I talk to Him throughout the day and night. My thoughts are so focused on everyone who lost their lives I feel I'm sending them straight to God. I'm keeping "telling" God to give Vanessa strength and let her find inner peace to make it through. My heart breaks for Vanessa as she has a 7 month old she has to care for and be the one her daughters lean on. God, hold Vanessa up. Let her be able to mourn Kobe and Gianna.

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t think I’ve ever been this distraught over a “celebrities” death. Not that it’s any less meaningful, because at the end of the day, yes, they are still human beings, but some people don’t take it as serious because they don’t personally know them. No, I did not know Kobe, but this one hits hard. I don’t know what it is, but I can’t stop thinking about him and his beautiful daughter, those final moments they were together. As a mother, I can only imagine the anguish Vanessa is feeling right now, and it brings me to tears. I pray for her, their 3 other daughters and the rest of the families involved. We love you Kobe and Gigi! Rest in paradise 🙏🏽
